  "description": "Create Documents Subpage\n\nBuild a new /documents subpage that displays and manages document-related content within the application.\n\nRequirements:\n- Create a new route at /documents that integrates with existing routing structure\n- Design and implement the page layout following current application design patterns\n- Add navigation link to the documents page in the main menu or sidebar\n- Include appropriate page title and meta information\n- Implement basic document listing or placeholder content\n- Ensure the page is responsive across mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports\n- Add loading states and error handling for the page\n- Include appropriate authentication/authorization checks if required by the application\n\nConsiderations:\n- Determine what content/functionality the documents page should display (list view, grid view, upload interface, etc.)\n- Decide on data source for documents (API endpoint, static content, database query)\n- Consider pagination or infinite scroll if displaying multiple documents\n- Plan for empty states when no documents are available",
