      "description": "Create Documentation Website with Shareable Links\n\nBuild a documentation website that can be hosted and shared via URL links with team members and users.\n\nRequirements:\n- Set up a static documentation site using a documentation framework (e.g., Docusaurus, VitePress, MkDocs, or similar)\n- Configure hosting deployment (GitHub Pages, Vercel, Netlify, or similar platform)\n- Create initial documentation structure with placeholder content sections\n- Ensure the site generates a publicly accessible URL that can be shared\n- Include a navigation system for browsing documentation pages\n- Set up automatic deployment pipeline when documentation is updated\n- Add basic styling and branding consistent with the project\n\nConsiderations:\n- Determine if authentication/access control is needed or if the site should be publicly accessible\n- Decide on documentation organization structure (getting started, API reference, guides, etc.)\n- Consider SEO optimization for documentation discoverability\n- Plan for versioning if multiple product versions need separate documentation",
